Build a full-stack multilingual social feed app called "Mwitter" (part of the Melify platform).

## STACK
- Backend: Node.js + Express + node:sqlite (--experimental-sqlite flag, Node 22+)
- Frontend: Vanilla JS class (MTKTwitter), SCSS, no frameworks
- Auth: JWT (7d), bcryptjs
- Port: 3002

## FILE STRUCTURE
twitter.local/
├── server.js
├── melify.db (auto-created)
├── package.json  (express, bcryptjs, jsonwebtoken, cors, dotenv)
└── public/
    ├── index.html          (host page, loads all CSS/JS)
    ├── mtk-twitter.html    (BARE: only <mtk-twitter> tag, NO scripts)
    ├── user.html           (dark admin page, click row to auto-login)
    ├── css/
    │   ├── mtk-twitter.scss
    │   └── mtk-twitter.css (compiled)
    └── js/
        ├── mtk-twitter.js
        └── mtk-twitter.config.js

## BACKEND (server.js)
- express.json({ limit: '10mb' })
- Auto-creates SQLite DB with tables: users, tweets, likes, retweets, bookmarks
- JWT auth middleware (authRequired / authOptional)
- Endpoints:
  POST   /api/auth/register
  POST   /api/auth/login
  GET    /api/users/me
  PATCH  /api/users/me
  GET    /api/users/:username
  GET    /api/tweets?lang=&since=
  POST   /api/tweets
  GET    /api/tweets/:id
  DELETE /api/tweets/:id
  GET    /api/tweets/:id/replies
  POST   /api/tweets/:id/replies
  POST   /api/tweets/:id/like
  DELETE /api/tweets/:id/like
  POST   /api/tweets/:id/retweet
  DELETE /api/tweets/:id/retweet
  POST   /api/tweets/:id/bookmark
  DELETE /api/tweets/:id/bookmark
  GET    /api/bookmarks
  GET    /api/tweets/:id/translate?target=
  POST   /api/upload  (base64 → saves to public/uploads/, returns URL)
  GET    /api/health
- Translation: Google Translate unofficial API (translate.googleapis.com/translate_a/single?client=gtx), DB cache, client dict fallback
- Seed users on first run (password: demo1234):
  mel (en, verified), josh (he), priyasharma (hi), carlosmendoza (es, verified),
  kenjitanaka (ja, verified), omarhassan (ar), natasha_v (ru), farid (fa)
- Each seed user gets one seed tweet in their native language

## FRONTEND ARCHITECTURE
- MTKTwitter vanilla JS class in mtk-twitter.js
- Auto-initializes: window.mtkTwitterInstance = new MTKTwitter('mtk-twitter.mtk-twitter')
- wc pub/sub bus (window.wc) for cross-component events
- MTK_TWITTER_CONFIG object in mtk-twitter.config.js
- index.html loads scripts normally (NOT via wc-include eval)
- mtk-twitter.html contains ONLY <mtk-twitter class="mtk-twitter"> — no scripts

## SCREENS
1. Splash — app preview, create account / sign in buttons, theme toggle
2. Register — name, username, email, password (strength meter), language select
3. Login — username/email + password
4. App — full layout (see below)

## APP LAYOUT (3-column desktop, mobile-first)
### Topbar (sticky)
- Brand logo (hidden on desktop): "Mwitter" in Keania One font
- Title #mtk-topbar-title: "Mwitter" in Keania One, primary color — always fixed
- Language picker button, theme toggle, avatar (opens profile menu)
- max-width: 1200px, margin: 0 auto

### Left Sidebar (desktop only, 240px)
- Nav items: My Mweets, Explore, Notifications, Messages, Bookmarks, Profile
- "Post" button (gradient, pill shape)
- Theme toggle button (Light/Dark mode label)
- User card at bottom (avatar, display name, @handle)
- ALL labels translate with display language

### Feed (center, max 600px)
- Feed header (sticky): shows user's display_name on Home, section name otherwise
- Language pill showing current display language
- Compose box: avatar + textarea + image button + emoji picker + char count + Post button
  - Image: prompt for URL first, fallback to file upload; uploads base64 to /api/upload
  - Emoji: 50-emoji picker panel, inserts at cursor, closes after pick
- Tweet list with grouping (one visible tweet per user, rest collapsed behind "N more" expand button)
- New posts banner (sticky, primary color) when polling finds new tweets — stays until clicked
- Polling every 8s

### Tweet card features
- Avatar, name, verified badge, @handle, language badge, relative timestamp
- Fresh tweets (<90s): timestamp in primary color
- Auto-translation: Google Translate API → shows translated text + "Show original" toggle
- RTL support for Hebrew, Arabic, Persian
- Actions: Reply (opens thread panel), Repost, Like, Bookmark, Delete (own tweets only)
- Reply dot indicators: 🔵 blue dot on sender's tweet, 🔴 red dot + 1px dashed red border on receiver's tweet — cleared when thread is opened
- Expand/collapse grouped tweets from same user

### Thread panel (slide in from right)
- Shows original tweet + all replies + reply compose
- Esc or back button closes
- Auto-translates all tweets in thread

### Right Sidebar (desktop, 300px)
- Search box
- Trending widget with 5 hashtags
- ALL text translates with display language

### Bottom nav + FAB (mobile only)

### Profile menu (dropdown from avatar)
- Profile, Change Language, Light/Dark mode, Sign Out
- ALL labels translate

## LANGUAGES (14 total, stored as display preference separate from posting language)
en 🇺🇸, hi 🇮🇳, he 🇮🇱 (RTL), ar 🇸🇦 (RTL), es 🇪🇸, fr 🇫🇷, de 🇩🇪,
zh 🇨🇳, pt 🇧🇷, ja 🇯🇵, ru 🇷🇺, ko 🇰🇷, it 🇮🇹, fa 🇮🇷 (RTL)

## TRANSLATION BEHAVIOR
- Display language ≠ posting language (stored separately in localStorage)
- Switching display language re-translates ALL visible tweets in-place
- Translation priority: DB cache → Google Translate API → client dict fallback
- "Show original" / "Show in [language]" toggle on each translated tweet
- All UI strings (nav, buttons, search, trending, menus) translate too

## THEME
- Dark (default) / Light toggle, persisted in localStorage
- SCSS variables via CSS custom properties
- Fonts: DM Sans (UI), Source Serif 4 (tweet body), Keania One (Mwitter brand)

## SCSS
- Single file, all scoped to .mtk-twitter
- Dark theme default, .mtk-twitter--light override
- --h-pad: 20px, --host-topbar: 0px CSS variables
- Mobile-first, breakpoints at 768px and 1024px
- #mtk-topbar-title: Keania One, primary color

## user.html (admin)
- Dark themed, lists all users from API
- Click any row to auto-login as that user (fetches JWT, stores in localStorage)
- Shows avatar, display name, @handle, language (with flag), RTL badge, email, join date
- Languages map includes all 14 languages including fa 🇮🇷
- RTL set includes: he, ar, fa

## KEY BEHAVIORS
- Auto-logout on 401 (stale session)
- JWT stored in localStorage as mtk_session
- Bookmarks: one per user enforced (server + client)
- Delete tweet: optimistic removal with slide-out animation
- Desktop notifications when tab not focused
- Polling: smart grouping-aware prepend
- index.html loads scripts as <script src="..."> tags — NOT inside wc-include HTML
- mtk-twitter.html must be BARE (no script tags) to avoid jQuery globalEval errors
